curtis thomas e real estate developer banker and founder of the curtis supermarket chain died friday of a stroke born in boston mr curtis developed more than two million square feet of commercial space in southeastern massachusetts he was a community leader and contributed greatly to a variety of charities after losing his eldest son tom jr an allamerican sailor at georgetown university tom sr became active in promoting the gu sailing team with grants gifts and scholarships he also established an educational scholarship at st anselms college the alma mater of his eldest daughter kathleen who died in 1993 tom and his wife marjorie resided in palm beach gardens fl and summered in hingham ma beloved husband of marjorie e pearce curtis loving father of brian p curtis of hingham ma elizabeth a curtis of new york ny dianne m curtis of hingham sarah c hanlon of hingham and jonathan p curtis of hingham devoted brother of mary richard david alan jean and dorothy loving papa of 14 grandchildren funeral mass in st paul 's church hingham wednesday august 16 at 10 am in lieu of flowers donations may be made to the lincoln sailing center po box 492 hingham ma 02043

